All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Bullet
Bullet class is capable of representing a projectile.
BulletTest
 
Coin
Coin class is a game object that the player can touch to pick up.
Collider
The Collider allows for performing collision detection.
Entity
Entity is a universal game object that participates in an entity system.
EntityEvent
EntityEvent is a container for event classes.
EntityTest
 
Explosion
Explosion class represents an explosion in the game.
FrameRateTracker
FrameRateTracker is a tool for keeping track of how much time has passed.
Game
The Main Game class.
GameOverPane
GameOverPane places itself ontop of the game to inform the player that the game is over and telling the player they can submit their game for a score.
GamePane
GamePane is the pane that is responsible for presenting the game to the player.
GameTest
 
Graphics
Graphics is responsible for drawing all the sprites from Game over to a canvas so the player can see the game.
HealthBar
HealthBar represents a health bar.
House
House represents an obstruction to the invaders (and even the player).
Input
Input is responsible for handling all input from the player.
Invader
The Invader class is responsible for all Invader logic.
InvaderCluster
InvaderCluster contains Invaders to move and manage.
InvaderGoal
InvaderGoal only serves to be a line which seperates the invaders from the player.
InvaderTest
 
InvaderType
InvaderType enum for invaders to keep track of what invader type/sprite they represent.
KeyBinding
KeyBinding class is responsible for representing a single keybind.
KeyBinding.Type
Enum representing various types of key bindings along with their descriptions.
KeyBindingsPane
KeybindingsPane contains all the keybindings given by other classes.
LeaderboardPane
LeaderboardPane contains the submitted names in the saved score file.
MainGUI
MainGUI is the start point of the java application which manages all the subpanes and allows switching between panes using a stack.
MenuPane
Menu pane contains the actual buttons for each button option.
OptionsPane
Option pane contains all the settings that can be changed for the game, such as sound, wireframes, and keybinds settings.
Player
Player class is responsible for allowing the player to interact with the game.
PlayerTest
 
Rect
Rect types of Entity allow for representing an entity as a rectangle instead of just a point.
Score
The score class contains the current score of the game.
SoundPlayer
SoundPlayer is responsible for loading and playing song and sounds.
Sprite
Sprite is a rectangle entity that contains one or many images which it can cycle through and return when the rendering loop needs it.
Sprites
Sprites is responsible for keeping a cache of all the images for the game.
Team
Representation of teams.
Turret
Turrets are objects similar to the player and invaders.
